{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7b0eff22-c1ca-4218-b717-f98fc0c6e43e","content":"Yes, you'll hit **target framework compatibility issues**. MSTest v3 drops support for:\n\n- **`net5.0`** — .NET 5 is out of support; you must use **.NET 6+**\n- **`net462`** — .NET Framework older than **4.6.2** is dropped (yours is exactly 4.6.2, so it's borderline — it *should* work, but 4.7.2+ is recommended)\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — also dropped; you need **.NET 6+**\n\n### What to do\n\nUpdate your `TargetFrameworks` before migrating. A compatible replacement would be:\n\n```xml\n<TargetFrameworks>net8.0;net472</TargetFrameworks>\n```\n\nThen upgrade MSTest packages to v3. Would you like me to perform the full migration, or do you need more details on other breaking changes (e.g., assertion overloads, `DataRow` constructors, timeout behavior)?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"264d33f0-31dc-4603-b1b6-1fdf52a38eff","outputTokens":240,"requestId":"63E3:343824:3BA6A49:41D70DC:6A02FAE0"},"id":"60d6d3d1-6f96-47b9-b3b3-bfb5552b5969","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:03:20.513Z","parentId":"a5087ea0-e09b-4e2e-888c-6919972a0481"}
